1) Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) is an object storage service that offers industry-leading scalability, data availability, security, and performance.
2) Focused on general object storage on the cloud
3) It can be stores big files, small files, media content, source code, meta data, spread sheets, etc.. up to max 5TB a single object with minimum cost.
4) Scalable, Highly Available, Durable, Supports integration with AWS.
5) Useful in variety of contexts:
      i)   Website hosting
      ii)  Database backups
      iii) Data processing pipelines

Bucket: A bucket is a container for objects stored in Amazon S3. You can store any number of objects in a bucket and can have up to 100 buckets in your account as default.
-------
By Url: http://s3.amazonaws.com/<Bucket_Name>/<Object_Name>

Storage classes:
----------------
Amazon S3 offers a range of storage classes designed for different use cases. For example, you can store mission-critical production data in S3 Standard for frequent access, save costs by storing infrequently accessed data in S3 Standard-IA or S3 One Zone-IA, and archive data at the lowest costs in S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval, S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval, and S3 Glacier Deep Archive.



